<p><em>Note</em>: <code>watch</code> will only work when the request is made over a socket connection (e.g. using <code>socket.get</code>), <em>not</em> over an http connection (e.g. using <code>jquery.get</code>).</p>
<h3 id="blueprints-and-watch-" permalink="blueprints-and-watch()">Blueprints and .watch()</h3>
<blockquote>
<p>By default, the blueprint <code>find</code> and <code>findOne</code> actions will call <code>.watch()</code> on the model class.  This behavior can be changed for all models by setting the <code>sails.config.blueprints.autoWatch</code> to <code>false</code>, or for a specific model by setting <code>autoWatch</code> to <code>false</code> in the model&apos;s class file.</p>
</blockquote>
